%S A396962 3,5,5,7,7,47,199,199,122069,110437,110437,10780897,141188371,
%T A396962 141188371
%N A396962 Leading term of a 2 X n generalized arithmetic progression (GAP) of primes with smallest last term.
%C A396962 This sequence is a replacement for the incorrect A113830.
%C A396962 The 2 X k generalized arithmetic progression (GAP) of distinct primes with smallest last term is of the form a+b*i+c*j, with 0 <= i <= 1, and 0 <= j <= k-1.
%C A396962 a(n) for n = 3, 5, and 6 are smaller than A113830(n).
%C A396962 The list of the smallest 2 X k GAPs less than 10^9 ends at k = 15. The last term of the smallest 2 X 16 GAP will be greater than 10^9.
%H A396962 Jens Kruse Andersen, <a href="https://primerecords.dk/aprecords.htm">Primes in Arithmetic Progression Records</a> [May have candidates for later terms in this sequence.]
%H A396962 Andrew Granville, <a href="https://dms.umontreal.ca/~andrew/PDF/PrimePatterns.pdf">Prime number patterns</a>.
%e A396962 Table detailing the 2 X n GAPs, with 2 <= n <= 9:
%e A396962   n    GAP           Last term
%e A396962   2  3+8*i+2*j           13
%e A396962   3  5+2*i+6*j           19
%e A396962   4  5+2*i+12*j          43
%e A396962   5  7+4*i+30*j         131
%e A396962   6  7+100*i+30*j       257
%e A396962   7  47+132*i+210*j    1439
%e A396962   8  199+682*i+210*j   2351
%e A396962   9  199+3300*i+210*j  5179
%Y A396962 Cf. A005115, A113827, A133277, A391764, A396963.
%K A396962 nonn,more
%O A396962 2,1
